    • Method Detail

      • setResultOffset

        void setResultOffset(long start)
        The starting position from where to retrieve a page of resulting documents.
        This will switch off the default paging behaviour that use the cursormark, and use the classical start-size for paging request.


        It is not recommended to use page-start to retrieve a page that is very deep, i.e., the page-start is large. In those case, use cursormark for paging will have much better performance. Use it only the "start" value is small and u want to request that certain page only.

        Parameters:
        start -
